******
[3] Argentina
Date: Thu 23 Jun 2022
Source: Government of Argentina [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
https://www.argentina.gob.ar/noticias/salud-confirma-el-cuarto-caso-de-viruela-simica-en-el-pais


The National Ministry of Health confirms the 4th case of monkeypox in the country based on the positive result of the PCR test carried out by the National Institute of Infectious Diseases (INEI) of the National Administration of Laboratories and Health Institutes (ANLIS). This case is a 45 year old man who lives in Godoy Cruz, Mendoza province, and who had traveled to Spain in the last 21 days.

The person began to present a fever greater than 38 deg C [100.4 deg F], swollen lymph nodes and vesicular rashes on [15 Jun 2022], the suspected case was reported on the [19 Jun 2022] and the samples were sent to the national reference laboratory with a positive PCR result on [21 Jun 2022] for monkeypox. At the moment, his state of health is good and he is complying with the corresponding isolation.

The 1st case of monkeypox in the country was confirmed on [27 May 2022] in a 40 year old man living in the province of Buenos Aires with a history of travel to Spain. That same day, the 2nd case of this disease was also confirmed in a 49 year old man, a resident of Spain, visiting the province of Buenos Aires and with no connection to the 1st case. The 3rd was confirmed on [9 Jun 2022] in a 36 year old citizen residing in the Autonomous City of Buenos Aires and with no travel history. To date, no secondary cases have been registered from the 4 confirmed cases.

